(294, 1, '2023-04-11 15:54:33', '2023-04-11 15:54:33', 'Roberto Benigni, (born October 27, 1952, Misericordia, Arezzo, Italy), Italian actor and director known for his comedic work, most notably La vita è bella (1997; Life Is Beautiful), for which he won an Academy Award for best actor.\n\nBenigni was the son of a poor tenant farmer who had worked in a German forced-labour camp during World War II. The elder Benigni used humour in retelling his experiences, which helped shape his son’s comedic skill. Benigni briefly attended a Jesuit seminary in Florence, and, after a stint as a magician’s assistant, he joined an underground theatre group in the late 1960s.', 'Roberto Benigni', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'roberto-benigni', '', '', '2023-04-11 15:54:33', '2023-04-11 15:54:33', '', 0, 'http://tmdb_actor_id=4818', 0, 'actors', '', 0),
